From the name of the compound, we can see that it contains carbon (C), hydrogen (H), nitrogen (N), and possibly other elements depending on the functional groups present. 

Starting from the main chain, we have a propane backbone consisting of three carbon atoms (C), each of which is bonded to hydrogen atoms. The nitrogen atoms (N) are present in the side groups of the molecule - specifically, in the piperidine ring and in the dimethylamine functional groups. 

Counting the number of carbon atoms, hydrogen atoms, and nitrogen atoms in the molecule, we can construct the molecular formula of (2R)-2-N,2-N-dimethyl-1-N-piperidin-4-ylpropane-1,2-diamine as:
C10H24N3

This is the molecular formula of the compound based on the given chemical structure.
